    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>National Briefing | Washington: Emissions Bill Introduced</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew C. Revkin (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Revkin, Andrew C</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sens Robert C Byrd and Ted Stevens offer bill to establish for first time targets and timetables for stabilizing emissions of heat-trapping greenhouse gases (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Two senators from states rich in coal and oil introduced legislation that would for the first time establish targets and a timetable for stabilizing emissions of heat-trapping greenhouse gases, which are released mainly by burning fossil fuels. The senators, Robert C. Byrd, Democrat of West Virginia, and Ted Stevens, Republican of Alaska, said the legislation was necessary now that scientists had established a link between human actions and global warming.</p>
        <p>Andrew C. Revkin (NYT)</p>
      </block>
